        "committer": {
          "name": "Andreas Dilger",
          "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
          "date": "2026-04-29 04:56:26.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-18876 build: exclude more files for dpkg-buildpkg",
        "message": "LU-18876 build: exclude more files for dpkg-buildpkg\n\nRunning \"make debs\" generates a source tarball via \"dpkg-buildpkg\"\nrather than \"make dist\" or similar, but this includes everything\nin the tree.  It includes all of the previous binaries (.o, .ko),\nprevious tarballs from \"make debs\", etc.  This is very slow.\n\nGenerate the dpkg-buildpkg exclude list from the .gitignore file,\nso that it is kept relatively uptodate.  This appears to work well,\nbut keeps a static exclude list as a fallback in case the build is\nbeing done outside of a git checkout (e.g. from a tarball itself).\n\nAs a starting point, it only uses the top-level .gitignore file, but\ncould potentially be taught to use the subdirectory .gitignore files\nto exclude files in those subdirectories.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Andreas Dilger <adilger@thelustrecollective.com>\nChange-Id: I82c1fc20a4e06cae9088c43a6a737b1740500c1e\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
